Finding Python version on the command line
Which of the following commands will NOT show what version of Python is installed? Feel free to try out the various answers on the terminal.


$ python
Python 3.5.2 (default, Nov 23 2017, 16:37:01)
[GCC 5.4.0 20160609] on linux
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
$ python -V
Python 3.5.2
$ python --version
Python 3.5.2
$ which python
/usr/bin/python




python
python -V
python --version

#not - which python
Correct! which python shows the location where Python is installed on your machine. This does not always contain the version of Python in the folder name.

